Tropical Depression Forms Off California; Storm Gert May Weaken

-- B y   A n n   K o h
-- 
2011-08-16T03:51:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/tropical-depression-forms-off-california-storm-gert-may-weaken.html
A tropical depression about 1,690
miles (2,715 kilometers) west-southwest of  Baja California  is
moving away from the U.S. East Coast and may become a tropical
storm today, the National Hurricane Center said in an  advisory 
at 8 p.m. Los Angeles time yesterday.  The system is moving west at 9 miles per hour. Top winds
near 35 mph are forecast to undergo “some strengthening” in
the next couple of days, the center said.  Tropical Storm Gert in the Atlantic was 250 miles northeast
of  Bermuda  and was traveling north-northeast at 18 mph, the
center said in an  advisory  at 11 p.m. Miami time yesterday. The
storm is expected to begin weakening late today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ann Koh in Singapore at   akoh15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
